Author | Caijing No. 1 Chen Yikan

The number of people infected with COVID-19 pneumonia is still on the rise and the epidemic is spreading. Not only are there more cases of pneumonia in the "worst-hit areas" of Wuhan, but there is also a sharp increase in the number of people infected in Huanggang City in Hubei Province, next to Wuhan.

On January 25, the Health Commission of Hubei Province reported 180 new cases of COVID-19 pneumonia yesterday, with 77 new cases in Wuhan and 52 in Huanggang.

Huanggang City Health data on the 25th, as of yesterday, Huanggang's cumulative total of COVID-19 pneumonia cases, including 54 cases of Huangzhou District, Wuxue 5 cases.

In view of the grim situation, Huanggang new pneumonia prevention and control upgrade again, a "closed city" . On January 25, Huanggang's COVID-19 pneumonia prevention and control headquarters issued a notice that from 14:00 on the 25th, the city's traffic control. All expressways in the city will be closed, the intersection of downtown Huanggang and other counties (cities and districts) leaving the city will be closed, the provincial and county roads between the city and county (cities and districts) will be closed, and the provincial and county roads will be closed. All passenger ferries and steam ferries on the Yangtze River and inland rivers in the city have been suspended.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Data Source: Huanggang City Health Commission

"there are a lot of patients in the fever clinic, and I sent support from other hospitals, and a lot of people are waiting to see the doctor, " a staff member of the fever clinic at Huangzhou District people's Hospital in Huanggang told China Business News. The hospital was identified by the local government as one of Huanggang's COVID-19 fever clinics.

Wuxue's First People's Hospital fever clinic staff told the first financial, now every day there are more than 200 people to the clinic, our medical staff did not rest, a little bit fast can not hold.

Wuxue First People's Hospital is the designated hospital for pneumonia with local COVID-19 infection. All five confirmed cases are being treated at the hospital. "The number of confirmed cases is likely to continue to increase because of the large number of people returning from Wuhan and Huanggang, " said the staff member.

The first finance reporter interviewed fever clinic of many hospitals in Huanggang. The medical staff all reported that there was a serious shortage of medical materials in the area.

"We are short of everything, including N95 masks, protective clothing, goggles and gloves, " a nurse at Huanggang Hospital of Traditional Chinese Medicine told China Business News.

Wuxue Red Cross Hospital staff told reporters that the N95 mask they wear has been used for several days, protective clothing is also very short, general medical supplies are short, which is a problem faced by all hospitals.

"We are buying N95 masks everywhere these days, but we can't get them, " said the Wuxue First People's Hospital staff member. "Now the hospital beds are full, and now we are taking over other places and opening new wards. ".

On January 24, the Huanggang COVID-19 Pneumonia Control Headquarters issued a notice saying that materials needed for epidemic prevention and control were urgently needed, iNCLUDING: Medical Equipment, medical equipment, reagents, drugs, protective equipment, decontamination equipment, consumables (one mask demand is larger) and so on. Huanggang Red Cross Society is responsible for receiving medical supplies, protective supplies and other special materials.

Huanggang Red Cross staff told reporters that yesterday Wuhan had two special supplies to Huanggang, we unified after receiving, will be issued by the city control headquarters. At present, the city is still in short supply of special materials, especially N95 masks, disinfectant, infrared thermometer, goggles and so on.

In order to curb the spread of the epidemic in Huanggang, from the 24th, the Huanggang City Bus, long-distance Passenger Transport suspended operations; urban rail stations, railway stations leaving the city of Huanggang access temporarily closed, no special reason, people do not leave the city; All cinemas, Internet cafes and indoor public cultural, tourist and entertainment venues in the urban area of Huanggang will be closed while the central Huangzhou District market will be closed.

Wuxue also suspended the operation of Urban Public Transport, long-distance passenger transport, ferry and steam ferry from 12 noon on the 24th. The Access Road leading from the Wuxue Wuxue City Railway Station is temporarily closed. Members of the public are advised not to leave the city for any special reason. Temporary closure of all cinemas, Internet cafes and indoor public culture, tourism and entertainment venues in the urban area of Wuxue.

In the city of Huanggang and Wuxue, all the city crossing, staff in accordance with the law and regulations on the passing of vehicles and personnel to carry out disease prevention and control, not missing a person a car. People in and out of the city for body temperature testing, fever symptoms of patients in a timely manner to the designated medical points for further examination and treatment; close contact with the car to the designated places for observation.

"At the moment, I basically stay at home and don't go out. I feel the atmosphere in Huangzhou is still very tense, " said Wang, a resident of Huangzhou District.

Staying at home as much as possible has become an option for many people in Huanggang. In Huanggang, Wuxue, Meichuan, Wuxue, for example, at 10:00 in the morning, one of the most congested streets in town center in years, is mostly deserted, with occasional cars passing through. People in the town are no longer visiting as they used to, and most of them are staying at home.

The Public Welfare Organization Wuxue Blue Sky Rescue Team Mr. Hu at the intersection of town, remind the streets of a small number of people who do not wear masks, put on masks, do not go out all right New Year. He told China Business News that he observed 90 percent of people on the street wearing masks. A small number of people who do not wear masks go out, but also to buy masks. But the town's out of masks by now.

"people are pretty self-conscious about wearing masks when they go out, but it's all about persistence, " said a Huanggang resident.
